Content Analyst (Arabic Language) - Deals & Private Equity, Bangalore

The Content Analyst role is within Deals Content team responsible for collection, maintenance, analysis and dissemination of high-quality information. The role involves providing clients with data related to Mergers and Acquisitions, Public Equity Offerings and Private Equity. The analyst would be responsible for researching and collecting relevant data and ensuring the data is provided in a timely and accurate manner. The individual will be required to support the team in day to day production tasks along with handling content queries and other requirements like projects and cleanses.

The position is offered on local terms and will require working in shifts. The position will report to the Team Leader, Deals.

Essential Day-to-Day Responsibilities:

Process and maintain data accurately and in a timely manner onto databases.
To research, source and collect information from various sources such as Companies Filings, Amendments, Press Releases, external news sources or announcements made by the company.
Ensures data quality, accuracy, timeliness and completeness per company standards for their covered product/market.
Basic knowledge of financial regulations and market practices/conventions in relevant markets.
Makes recommendations for process improvements to immediate manager.
Works independently within defined area, taking ownership of problems within own area of knowledge.
Adhere to change control procedures, Content Operations standards and current data policies and procedures.

Competencies:

Candidate must possess a Bachelor's/College Degree in Business Administration/ Management, Marketing, Accountancy or any Financial related course;
Excellent communication skills in English and comfortable in using Business Communications over phone or email;
Dexterity to work in a team environment and has excellent interpersonal skills;
Comfortable working in a fast-paced environment as clients demand more real-time data exchange;
Understand financial statements and be able to explain to stakeholders

Core Skill sets:

Basic computer and internet research knowledge are required;
Willingness to take absolute responsibility for work tasks;
Ability to prioritize tasks and work effectively under pressure;
Ability to work both independently and as part of a team;
Willingness to work in Shifts (24/5) and during public/national holidays;
Self-motivated even when attending to routine tasks;
Ability to follow company policies;

LSEG is a leading global financial markets infrastructure and data provider. Our purpose is driving financial stability, empowering economies and enabling customers to create sustainable growth.

Our purpose is the foundation on which our culture is built. Our values of Integrity, Partnership, Excellence and Change underpin our purpose and set the standard for everything we do, every day. They go to the heart of who we are and guide our decision making and everyday actions.

Working with us means that you will be part of a dynamic organisation of 25,000 people across 65 countries. However, we will value your individuality and enable you to bring your true self to work so you can help enrich our diverse workforce. You will be part of a collaborative and creative culture where we encourage new ideas and are committed to sustainability across our global business. You will experience the critical role we have in helping to re-engineer the financial ecosystem to support and drive sustainable economic growth. Together, we are aiming to achieve this growth by accelerating the just transition to net zero, enabling growth of the green economy and creating inclusive economic opportunity.

LSEG offers a range of tailored benefits and support, including healthcare, retirement planning, paid volunteering days and wellbeing initiatives.

We are proud to be an equal opportunities employer. This means that we do not discriminate on the basis of anyone's race, religion, colour, national origin, gender, sexual orientation, gender identity, gender expression, age, marital status, veteran status, pregnancy or disability, or any other basis protected under applicable law. Conforming with applicable law, we can reasonably accommodate applicants and employees religious practices and beliefs, as well as mental health or physical disability needs.

Please take a moment to read this privacy notice carefully, as it describes what personal information London Stock Exchange Group (LSEG) (we) may hold about you, what it's used for, and how it's obtained, your rights and how to contact us as a data subject.

If you are submitting as a Recruitment Agency Partner, it is essential and your responsibility to ensure that candidates applying to LSEG are aware of this privacy notice.

